U.K.’s Carclo Says Business Is in Line With Company Forecasts

-- B y   D a v i d   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-08-12T06:53:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/u-k-s-carclo-says-business-is-in-line-with-company-forecasts.html
Carclo Plc (CAR) , a U.K. maker of wire and
plastics for electronics companies, said today business
continues in line with its forecasts.  Carclo’s financial position remains strong and it foresees
a further year of progress, the Ossett, West Yorkshire-based
company said in a statement distributed on the Regulatory News
Service.  The company’s re-financing should be completed ahead of
schedule after “good progress” in discussions with its banks,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 David Goodman  in London at 
 dgoodman28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  